8 An Act relating to schools; creating the President
Donald J. Trump Physical Fitness Act; providing short
9 title; directing the State Department of Education to
establish certain guidelines to administer certain
10 physical fitness test; directing guidelines to be
based on certain recommendations; providing for
11 contents of guidelines; requiring school districts to
administer certain test after certain guidelines have
12 been established; directing school districts to use
student performance results in certain manner;
13 providing for promulgation of rules; providing for
noncodification; providing for codification; and
14 providing an effective date.
15
16
17
18
19 AMENDMENT NO. 1. Strike the title, enacting clause, and entire bill
and insert:
20
21
22 "An Act relating to schools; creating the President
Donald J. Trump Physical Fitness Act; providing short
23 title; directing the State Department of Education to
establish certain guidelines to administer certain
24 physical fitness test; directing guidelines to be
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1437 Page 1

1 based on certain recommendations; providing for
contents of guidelines; requiring school districts to
2 administer certain test after certain guidelines have
been established; directing school districts to use
3 student performance results in certain manner;
providing for promulgation of rules; providing for
4 noncodification; providing for codification; and
providing an effective date.
5
6
7
8 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
9 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law not to be
10 codified in the Oklahoma Statutes reads as follows:
11 This act shall be known and may be cited as the “President
12 Donald J. Trump Physical Fitness Act”.
13 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 11-103.9c of Title 70, unless
15 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. The State Department of Education shall establish guidelines
17 for school districts in this state to assess the overall fitness of
18 students and encourage physical activity and healthy habits by
19 administering the Presidential Fitness Test. The physical fitness
20 test guidelines shall be based on the recommendations of the
21 President’s Council on Sports, Fitness, and Nutrition, which was
22 reconstituted by Executive Order 14327. The guidelines shall
23 include:
24 1. Training for personnel to administer the test;
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1437 Page 2

1 2. Exemption guidelines for students with disabilities, medical
2 conditions, or other factors that would impact their ability to
3 complete the test; and
4 3. An option for a parent or legal guardian of a student to opt
5 the student out of the test.
6 B. Upon development of the physical fitness test
7 recommendations by the President’s Council on Sports, Fitness, and
8 Nutrition and the subsequent establishment of guidelines by the
9 State Department of Education, school districts in this state shall
10 administer the Presidential Fitness Test to students using the
11 guidelines established pursuant to subsection A of this section or
12 from nationally accepted fitness testing programs designed for
13 school-aged children that test cardiovascular fitness, muscular
14 strength and endurance, flexibility, and body composition.
15 C. School districts shall utilize student performance results
16 on the Presidential Fitness Test to:
17 1. Promote the physical and mental benefits of daily movement,
18 exercise, and good nutrition;
19 2. Modify physical activity opportunities offered to students;
20 and
21 3. Encourage participation in physical activities available to
22 students inside and outside the school setting.
23 D. The State Board of Education may promulgate rules to
24 implement the provisions of this section.
ENGR. H. A. to ENGR. S. B. NO. 1437 Page 3

1 SECTION 3. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026."
2 Passed the House of Representatives the 6th day of May, 2026.
